From 3548c9cf11a12f6b5ed8ebadb7259bac04a8d95f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Date: Tue, 19 May 2026 11:17:41 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] hybris: disable distributed-file capability (no hmdfs driver)

The Halium/MTK 5.10 kernel has no hmdfs filesystem driver. With
const.distributed_file_property.enabled=true, storage_daemon's MountHmdfs()
attempts the real `-t hmdfs` mount, which fails ENODEV and aborts the
entire per-user mount sequence -- MountSharefs() and MountAppdata() never
run, so normal apps see an empty /storage/Users.

Setting it false routes MountHmdfs() through LocalMount() (plain bind
mounts only, no hmdfs driver needed) so the rest of the chain runs.

See legacy_sharefs_user_files.md.

Change-Id: I7101cbbc7e2f2a0e3639a9943bab1a709ba38bda
Signed-off-by: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 services/distributed_file.para | 9 ++++++++-
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/services/distributed_file.para b/services/distributed_file.para
index 901aa74cd..c5665d87f 100644
--- a/services/distributed_file.para
+++ b/services/distributed_file.para
@@ -12,6 +12,13 @@
 # limitations under the License.
 
 
-const.distributed_file_property.enabled=true
+# hybris_generic: the Halium/MTK 5.10 kernel has no hmdfs filesystem driver,
+# so the distributed-file capability is unavailable on this build.  Leaving
+# this `true` makes storage_daemon's MountHmdfs() attempt the real `-t hmdfs`
+# mount, which fails with ENODEV and aborts the entire per-user mount
+# sequence (MountSharefs + MountAppdata never run -> /storage/Users empty for
+# normal apps).  `false` routes MountHmdfs() through LocalMount() (plain bind
+# mounts only, no hmdfs driver needed) so the rest of the chain runs.
+const.distributed_file_property.enabled=false
 const.distributed_file_only_for_same_account_test=true
 
